<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2051&amp;p=10351#p10351"><![CDATA[
Because of declining eyesight, I use Windows 7 on a 1080p monitor at 125% screen resolution with a 13 pt. Calibri font. This works great for me everywhere I can change it. <span style="text-decoration: underline">Problem</span> here is I've not been able to find a way to change Start Menu and Toolbar Menu font(s). Starting with W7 Aero Segoe UI default font, all that happens to start menus and toolbar menus is their fonts enlarge slightly.<br /><br />Does anyone know how to change these fonts? I think it would be great (for me) to have some better control over what I read on-screen.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=381">RetiredEngineer</a> — Fri Jan 24, 2014 3:47 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
